As shown in Fig. 4a, a GFC was assembled layer by layer on a flexible PET substrate to harvest the biochemical energy from glucose molecules. The components include anode, gold (Au) electrode, PET substrate, cathode, and fixture. When the GFC was immersed into glucose solution, glucose molecules will be oxidized to gluconic acid at anode. Electrons flowed from anode to the cathode through the external circuit and generated electric current. The dissolved oxygen around cathode accepted electrons and combined with hydrogen ions to form water molecules (Fig. 4b). The redox reaction equations are as follows [41, 42]:Fig. 4
